==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trenchant
<hw>Trench"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>trenchant</ets>, F. <ets>tranchant</ets>, p. pr. See
<er>Trench</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fitted to
trench or cut; gutting; sharp.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Trenchant</xex> was
the blade.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Keen; biting; severe; <as>as,
<ex>trenchant</ex> wit</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trenchantly</ent>⟦br⟧
